## Workflow

### Sprint Backlog Breakdown (for Sprint Planning)

1. **For each backlog item, create a {{ work_tracking.work_item_types.feature }}** (not a {{ work_tracking.work_item_types.task }}!)

2. **Use Extended Thinking to:**
   - Decompose {{ work_tracking.work_item_types.feature }} into 2-5 child {{ work_tracking.work_item_types.task }}s
   - Generate comprehensive description for {{ work_tracking.work_item_types.feature }}
   - Generate comprehensive description for each {{ work_tracking.work_item_types.task }}
   - Define acceptance criteria (minimum 3 per item)
   - Identify technical requirements
   - Document implementation approach

3. **Define {{ work_tracking.work_item_types.feature }} with:**
   - Complete deliverable scope
   - **FULL description (500+ chars) with all required sections**
   - Acceptance criteria (5+ items)
   - Story point estimate (3-8 points)
   - Business value statement
   - Technical requirements
   - Risk assessment

4. **Define each child {{ work_tracking.work_item_types.task }} with:**
   - Action-oriented title (verb + object)
   - **FULL description (500+ chars) with all required sections**
   - Acceptance criteria (3+ items)
   - Story points (1-2 points)
   - Dependencies
   - Test requirements
   - Implementation notes

